<F P=101> Political </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hu Jintao Says Dalai Lama's `Basic Stand' on Tibet Unchanged </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2402041594 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 23 Feb 
94 Morning Edition p 6 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2402041594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Katsuhiko Iino] </F>
  [Text] Beijing, 22 Feb -- Hu Jintao, member of the 
Standing Committee of the CPC Political Bureau, met with a 
delegation of the Japan New Party (with Diet Member Banri Kaieda 
as delegation chief) currently visiting China on 22 February. 
During the meeting, Hu commented on Tibetan spiritual leader 
Dalai Lama XIV's recent proposal for a federation between the 
Chinese Government and a Tibetan autonomous government. Hu 
indicated that "the Dalai Lama has only changed his approach on 
the issue. There is no change in his basic stand." Thus, he 
disclosed that there is no change in China's stand of rejecting 
dialogue with the Dalai Lama. 

</TEXT>

