<F P=100> Central Eurasia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jiang, Others Meet With Azerbaijan's Aliyev </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0803013894 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1337 
GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW0803013894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 7 (XINHUA) -- Chinese President Jiang 
Zemin said here today that China attaches great importance to 
its ties with Azerbaijan and intends through common effort to 
further develop such friendly cooperation in every field. 
  Jiang made these remarks during talks with visiting 
Azerbaijani President Geydar Aliyev here this afternoon. 
  He said China and Azerbaijan are both in Asia, and their 
peoples' friendly contacts can be traced back to the "Silk Road" 
of more than 2,000 years ago. 
  The Chinese people have always harbored friendly sentiments 
toward the hardworking and wise people of Azerbaijan, which has 
a long history of culture, he said. 
  Jiang said Azerbaijan's independence and the establishment 
of 
diplomatic relations between the two countries have laid good 
conditions for the growth of bilateral ties. 
  Noting that the two countries have established contacts and 
cooperation in every aspect, Jiang said bilateral relations are 
now advancing in a healthy and steady way. 
  Jiang said the two countries also can strengthen and 
coordinate cooperation in international affairs and the United 
Nations. 
  He expressed the belief that the president's current visit 
to 
China will surely help raise bilateral relations and cooperation 
to a new level, as the two sides will sign a 
Sino-Azerbaijan joint statement and other documents on bilateral 
cooperation. 
  On the Nagorno-Karabakh conflict, Jiang said China is deeply 
concerned about the escalation of the conflict, the large number 
of people who have been wounded or killed, and the great loss of 
property during the conflict. 
  He said both sides of the conflict have paid a great price. 
It will bring no benefit to the two sides to delay the 
settlement of the conflict. 
  "We sincerely hope that Azerbaijan and Armenia will properly 
settle the conflict through peaceful negotiations as early as 
possible," Jiang said. 
  President Aliyev said that Azerbaijan places great 
importance 
on China's role and influence as a big nation in the 
international political and economic arena. 
  He said that his country is looking attentively and with 
great interest at the smooth execution of China's reform 
movement. 
  China has made tremendous achievements in its reforms, the 
visiting president said, adding that the Azerbaijani Government 
and people are willing to learn from China's experiences. 
  He expressed the belief that his current China visit will 
push Azerbaijani-Chinese ties to a new stage. 
  The two leaders shared the view during the talks that the 
five principles of peaceful co-existence should be the norms for 
handling state-to-state relations. 
  The leaders also briefed each other on their respective 
countries' domestic situations and foreign policies. 
  Among those attending the talks on the Chinese side were Qi 
Huaiyuan, director of the Foreign Affairs Office of the State 
Council, Yin Dakui, chairman of the Chinese Government Reception 
Committee and vice-minister of public health, and Dai Bingguo, 
vice-minister of foreign affairs. 
  Viktor Kuliyev, first deputy prime minister of Azerbaijan 
[name and position as received], Gasan Gasanov, minister of 
foreign affairs, Ali Insanov, minister of public health, and 
Sabir Rustamkhanly, press minister [name and position as 
received], also took part in the talks. 
  Prior to the talks, Jiang presided over a welcoming ceremony 
in the central hall of the Great Hall of the People for his 
Azerbaijani counterpart. Tomur Dawamad, vice-chairman of the 
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress of China 
(NPC), attended the ceremony. 
  In the evening, Jiang held a banquet for the Azerbaijani 
president and his party. 
  Aliyev arrived here on an official visit to China this 
morning by special plane, at the invitation of President Jiang. 
  He is the first Azerbaijani president to visit China since 
Azerbaijan gained its independence. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

