<H3> <TI>   Baku Radio Reports Aliyev Begins Visit to PRC </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0703170594 Baku Radio Baku International Service in Azeri 
1300 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0703170594 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Radio Baku International Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Azeri </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Geydar Aliyev has begun his official visit 
to the PRC. The visit will give an opportunity for the 
improvement of the political, economic, and cultural relations 
between the two countries. 
  President Aliyev received Ambassador Xia Shuyuan before 
leaving for the PRC and discussed matters related to the 
improvement of the relations between the two countries. Aliyev 
said that his visit to the PRC will be a very important event in 
Azerbaijan's history. He described the PRC as one of the 
largest countries in the world, which, as one of the permanent 
members of the UN Security Council, has an important role in 
world politics. 
  Special attention was focused on cooperation between 
Azerbaijan and the PRC in the economic, cultural, scientific, 
and technological fields. 
  For his part, Ambassador Xia Shuyuan said that his country's 
people and leaders have highly assessed President Geydar 
Aliyev's visit and noted that it will be of historic importance 
to Azerbaijan. 

</TEXT>

