<H3> <TI>   PRC Reports Phnom Penh Attack on Pailin 4 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0603151494 Beijing China Radio International in Cambodian 
1030 GMT 6 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0603151494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing China Radio International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Cambodian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ek Sereivoat, state secretary for national defense, 
disclosed on 5 March that the Khmer Royal Armed Forces began an 
offensive on 4 March against Pailin, the biggest stronghold of 
the Party of Democratic Kampuchea [PDK]. He said the attack was 
launched from areas south and north of Pailin city, but he did 
not reveal the scale of the attack or the number of the troops 
involved. 
  It was reported on 4 March that the PDK's main forces had 
already been withdrawn from Pailin. 

</TEXT>

