<H3> <TI>   Israel Economic, Trade Office Opens in Taipei </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0803101894 Taipei CNA in English 0727 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0803101894 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei CNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Lilian Wu] </F>
  [Text] Taipei, March 8 (CNA) -- The Israel Economic and 
Trade Office formally opened Monday [7 March] in Taipei. 
  Israeli representative Jacob Fass, 46, told reporters he was 
honored to be here. Fass, a career diplomat, explained that his 
office would work to promote trade, investment and tourism 
relations between Israel and Taiwan. 
  The office will also handle visa applications, most of which 
can be processed in two days, Fass said. 
  Trade between Israel and Taiwan totaled US$500 million in 
1993, with Taiwan enjoying a trade surplus of US$100 million. 
  Taiwan's major export items to Israel include personal 
computers, textiles and motorcycles, totaling US$300 million, 
while Israel exported US$200 million worth of goods to Taiwan 
last year, mainly hi-tech products, such as telecommunications, 
medical, aerospace and computer items. 
  In June, a large delegation representing some of the biggest 
companies and banks in Israel will visit Taiwan to explore 
possible business opportunities here, Fass said. 
  A Taipei Economic and Trade Office opened in Israel last 
May. 

</TEXT>

